Summary of Key Points
This document explains how Digital Palette LLC ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our website and mobile applications ("Services"). Please review this policy carefully.
We collect only the information necessary to provide and improve our Services.
A cookie consent banner is active on our website to manage your tracking preferences.
Third-party services are limited to Facebook and Google for login and social sharing functionalities.
Your rights are covered under applicable laws including GDPR and, for residents in the USA, additional rights under laws such as the CCPA.
For more detailed inquiries or requests, please contact us.
Privacy Policy
At Digital Palette LLC, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains, in broad terms, how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal data when you use our Services. By accessing or using our Services, you agree to the practices described herein.
1. Introduction
This policy applies to piZap.com, the piZap mobile applications on iOS and Android, and our family of apps. Our registered address is: 140 W Franklin St. Ste 203 PMB 42, Monterey, CA 93940, USA.
2. Information We Collect
We collect information necessary to operate and improve our Services. The details remain broad to ensure flexibility in how we process and manage your data.
3. How We Use Your Information
Your information is used for providing and enhancing our Services, managing your account, and for general communication purposes. We keep our descriptions broad to allow for flexibility and legal compliance.
4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience. A cookie consent banner is available on our website. For more details, please refer to our
Cookie Policy
.
5. Data Rights and Legal Compliance
We ensure that your rights are protected under applicable laws, including the GDPR. In addition, for residents of the United States, particularly California, additional rights under laws such as the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) apply. Requests for data access, correction, or deletion are handled in accordance with the law.
6. Data Security and Breach Notification
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard your data. In the event of a data breach, we will notify you in accordance with legal requirements.
7. Third-Party Services
Our Services incorporate third-party functionalities provided by Facebook and Google, primarily for login and social sharing.
8. Children's Privacy
Our Services are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect data from users under 13, and any necessary parental consent processes remain deliberately broad.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page along with an updated effective date.
10. Contact Information
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or your data rights, please contact us at
support@pizap.com
.
Cookie Policy
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience. You may manage your cookie preferences via your browser settings.
